PHASE 0 – Base Setup (before any module)
1.	Decide stack
o	Example:
	Backend: Node / Laravel / Django / Spring
	Frontend: React / Vue / Blade / plain HTML
	DB: MySQL or PostgreSQL
2.	Create base project
o	Setup project structure.
o	Configure DB connection.
o	Add basic routing.
o	Add env config (DB, ports, etc.).
3.	Authentication & Users
o	User table
o	Roles: admin, staff
o	Login, logout, password hashing
________________________________________
PHASE 1 – Masters (create these first)
Everything else depends on these.
1.	Company Settings
o	Company name, address, GST, phone, logo.
o	Default invoice prefix, next invoice number.
o	Default tax configuration (CGST/SGST/IGST).
2.	Customer Master
o	Fields:
	Name
	Phone
	Billing address
	Delivery address (separate field for invoice print)
	GSTIN (optional)
o	Basic CRUD + search.
3.	Supplier Master
o	Name
o	Phone
o	Address
o	GSTIN
o	CRUD + search.
4.	Product / Item Master
o	Item name
o	SKU / Code
o	Category
o	Unit (pcs, kg, etc.)
o	Tax % (GST)
o	Purchase price
o	Selling price
o	Opening stock
o	Status (active/inactive)
o	CRUD + search.
5.	Chart of Accounts (COA)
Create base ledger heads:
o	Asset: Cash, Bank, Stock, Debtors, Input GST
o	Liability: Creditors, Output GST
o	Income: Sales
o	Expense: Purchase, Other Expenses
Store them as rows in accounts table.
After Phase 1 you should be able to: login, manage customers, suppliers, products, and have basic accounts list.
________________________________________
PHASE 2 – Inventory & Core Transactions (no POS yet)
Step 1: Inventory Engine
1.	Stock Movement Model
o	Table: stock_ledger
o	Fields: product_id, date, reference_type (purchase, sale, etc.), reference_id, qty_in, qty_out, closing_stock.
2.	When to write stock entries
o	On purchase invoice save → qty_in
o	On purchase return → qty_out
o	On sales invoice → qty_out
o	On sales return → qty_in
3.	Current stock
o	Either calculate from stock_ledger sum.
o	Or keep a current_stock field in product and update on every transaction.
Step 2: Purchase Invoice Module
1.	UI
o	Select supplier.
o	Invoice no & date (auto from settings, but editable).
o	Line items: product, qty, rate, discount, tax%.
o	Totals: subtotal, tax, grand total.
2.	Backend
o	Save header (supplier, date, total).
o	Save line items.
o	Update stock ledger: qty_in.
o	Create accounting entries:
	Dr Purchase
	Dr Input GST
	Cr Supplier (or Cash/Bank)
3.	Listing & View
o	Purchase invoice list page with filters.
o	Detail view & print simple purchase bill.
Step 3: Purchase Return
1.	UI
o	Select original purchase invoice or supplier.
o	Items with negative quantity or return quantity.
2.	Logic
o	Update stock (qty_out).
o	Accounting:
	Dr Supplier (or Cash/Bank)
	Cr Purchase
	Cr Input GST (reverse)
________________________________________
PHASE 3 – Sales Side (standard invoice first)
Step 1: Sales Invoice (Normal)
1.	UI
o	Select customer.
o	Billing address + delivery address (from master, editable).
o	Items: product, qty, rate, discount, tax%.
o	Totals: same pattern as purchase.
2.	Backend
o	Save header + items.
o	Update stock ledger with qty_out.
o	Accounting:
	Dr Customer (Debtor) or Cash/Bank
	Cr Sales
	Cr Output GST
3.	Printable Invoice
o	Template with:
	Company details
	Customer billing & delivery address
	Item table
	Tax split (CGST/SGST/IGST)
	Total amounts (in numbers + words if you want).
Step 2: Sales Return
1.	UI
o	Select original sales invoice or customer.
2.	Logic
o	Stock → qty_in.
o	Accounting:
	Dr Sales Return (or reduce Sales)
	Dr Output GST (reverse)
	Cr Customer (or Cash/Bank)
________________________________________
PHASE 4 – Payments, Receipts, Journal
Step 1: Payment & Receipt Vouchers
1.	UI
o	Payment:
	Date, Account (Cash/Bank), Payee (Supplier/Expense), Amount, Narration.
o	Receipt:
	Date, Account (Cash/Bank), Payer (Customer/Income), Amount, Narration.
2.	Backend
o	Payment:
	Dr Supplier / Expense
	Cr Cash/Bank
o	Receipt:
	Dr Cash/Bank
	Cr Customer / Income
3.	Link to invoices (optional first, can add later)
o	Voucher → linked invoice IDs for outstanding tracking.
Step 2: Journal Entry
1.	UI
o	Date, multiple lines:
	Account, Dr amount, Cr amount.
o	Total Dr must equal total Cr.
2.	Backend
o	Write to accounting ledger table.
________________________________________
PHASE 5 – Accounting Engine & Reports
Once all voucher types are working, build reports.
Step 1: Accounting Ledger
1.	Ledger Table / View
o	Store entries in account_ledger with:
	account_id, date, voucher_type, voucher_id, debit, credit, narration.
2.	Account-wise view
o	Filter by account & date range.
o	Opening balance + all transactions + closing balance.
Step 2: Trial Balance (Internal, to support P&L & Balance Sheet)
1.	Calculate
o	Sum debits & credits per account.
o	Ensure total debit = total credit (sanity).
Step 3: Profit & Loss
1.	Income & Expense accounts only
o	Income accounts → credit balance.
o	Expense accounts → debit balance.
2.	Output
o	List all income
o	List all expenses
o	Net profit or loss for period.
Step 4: Balance Sheet
1.	Assets, Liabilities, Capital
o	Assets = cash, bank, stock, debtors, etc.
o	Liabilities = creditors, GST payable, etc.
o	Capital = opening capital + retained earnings.
2.	Check
o	Assets = Liabilities + Capital.
________________________________________
PHASE 6 – Inventory Reports & Low Stock
1.	Stock Report
o	For each product:
	Opening stock
	Qty in
	Qty out
	Closing stock
2.	Low-Stock Alerts
o	Add reorder_level in product master.
o	Report: products where current_stock <= reorder_level.
3.	Inventory Valuation
o	Simple method first: closing_stock * latest_purchase_rate or average purchase rate.
________________________________________
PHASE 7 – POS Module (Retail Billing)
Do this only after normal sales invoice & inventory are stable.
1.	POS Screen UI
o	Big font, minimal clicks.
o	Product search by:
	Name / Code / Barcode.
o	Item grid with:
	Item name
	Qty
	Rate
	Total line.
o	Payment section:
	Mode: cash / UPI / card
	Received amount
	Balance to return.
2.	Backend
o	POS bill = special type of Sales Invoice:
	Same stock + accounting logic as sales invoice.
o	Auto-invoice number but separate series (e.g., POS-0001).
3.	Thermal Print Template (optional)
o	Smaller width.
o	Brief item details.
o	Total, payment mode, time.
________________________________________
PHASE 8 – WhatsApp & Export
Step 1: Sales Invoice WhatsApp Share
1.	Generate PDF
o	Use backend lib to output invoice PDF.
2.	Expose link / file
o	For web: generate URL, open system share or show QR.
o	For desktop: open WhatsApp Web URL with pre-filled message and link.
(Exact API usage depends on your stack and hosting; but architecturally, this is added after invoice and PDF are solid.)
Step 2: Export Functions
1.	Export to Excel/PDF
o	For: Ledger, P&L, Balance Sheet, Stock report, Sales & Purchase registers.
2.	Add buttons
o	Export to Excel / Export to PDF on each report page.
________________________________________
PHASE 9 – Dashboard & Polish
1.	Dashboard Widgets
o	Today’s sales amount.
o	Today’s number of invoices.
o	Total outstanding from customers.
o	Low-stock count.
o	Top 5 selling items (last 30 days).
2.	Search & Filters Everywhere
o	On all list screens (invoices, products, vouchers).
3.	User Permissions (if needed)
o	Role: which modules they can view/add/edit/delete.
________________________________________
Implementation Order – Short Checklist
Follow this exact order:
1.	Project setup + Auth
2.	Masters: Company, Customers, Suppliers, Products, Chart of Accounts
3.	Stock ledger + Inventory base
4.	Purchase Invoice → Purchase Return
5.	Sales Invoice (with delivery address in print) → Sales Return
6.	Payment & Receipt Vouchers
7.	Journal Entries
8.	Accounting ledger → Trial balance → P&L → Balance Sheet
9.	Inventory reports + Low-stock
10.	POS module
11.	Invoice PDF + WhatsApp share
12.	Exports (PDF/Excel)
13.	Dashboard + role permissions + UI polish

